  "prompt": "How long do spices last before going bad?",
  "response": "The shelf life of spices varies depending on whether they are whole or ground, and how they are stored. Here\u2019s a general guideline for how long spices last before they lose their potency or go bad:\n\n### **Whole Spices (e.g., peppercorns, cinnamon sticks, cloves, whole nutmeg)**\n- **Shelf Life:** 2\u20134 years\n30; Whole spices retain their flavor and potency longer than ground spices because their essential oils are protected by their intact structure.\n\n### **Ground Spices (e.g., cinnamon, cumin, paprika, turmeric)**\n- **Shelf Life:** 1\u20133 years\n30; Ground spices lose their flavor more quickly due to increased exposure to air and light.\n\n### **Herbs (e.g., dried basil, oregano, thyme)**\n- **Shelf Life:** 1\u20133 years\n30; Dried herbs lose their potency faster than whole spices but can last longer if stored properly.\n\n### **Seed Spices (e.g., cumin seeds, fennel seeds, mustard seeds)**\n- **Shelf Life:** 2\u20134 years\n30; Seeds typically last longer than ground spices but not as long as whole spices.\n\n### **Spice Blends (e.g., curry powder, chili powder, garam masala)**\n- **Shelf Life:** 1\u20132 years\n30; Blends lose their flavor more quickly because the individual components degrade at different rates.\n\n---\n\n### **Factors That Affect Shelf Life**\n1. **Storage Conditions:** Keep spices in a cool, dark, and dry place (e.g., a pantry or cabinet). Exposure to heat, light, and humidity speeds up degradation.\n2. **Container:** Use airtight containers to prevent air and moisture from entering.\n3. **Quality:** High-quality, fresh spices last longer than old or poorly stored ones.\n\n---\n\n### **Signs Your Spices Have Gone Bad**\n- Loss of aroma or flavor\n- Change in color (e.g., paprika fading from red to brown)\n- Clumping or hardening (due to moisture)\n- Musty or off smell\n\n---\n\nTo maximize freshness, buy spices in small quantities and label them with the purchase date. If you\u2019re unsure about a spice\u2019s potency, crush a small amount in your palm and smell it\u2014if the aroma is weak, it\u2019s time to replace it.",
